<!channel> , sorry for the random question but I'm getting ready to ditch ATT and was wondering if anyone had a good experience with Verizon or T-mobile (or any other carriers)?
I had really good experience with Verizon.
pro Verizon all the way.
i mean it's still a crappy process to go into the store and get help because it takes so long, but i've had their service since like 2006 and it's been great

I have T-mobile. Never had any complaints about customer service and I get fine service in the metro area, but when i go to the gorge or mt hood or anywhere else that's not very urban it's extremely unreliable.
It's caused me headaches on more than one occasion
Got it. Thank you all.
yeah - I mean, once you allow for the fact that they're all run by the very worst people in the world - I'd say Verizon.
<@U0260V4K1> Important caveat.
every time I get a new phone I look around to see which is the most ethical carrier. The answer is always: none of them.
I actually really loved verizon when I had them but don't know anymore.
i have a friend who switched to tmobile from att and she hates it.
<!channel> I'm starting to think more seriously about Have I Fed My Dog Today (iOS app). Anyone want to collaborate on it?
YES!!
The MVP is just a big button and maybe a timer ("yes I fed my dog today", plus system notification "maybe you should feed your dog soon...")
I have a Cat but that shouldn't matter. Right?

Future features may include (off the top of my head):

- multiple pets
- machine learning about when the dog likes to eat
- did it contain medication?
- did dog eat it all at once or save some for later?
- saved meals
- track pooping too
    - time
    - location
    - which direction dog is facing (<http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/dogs-poop-in-alignment-with-earths-magnetic-field-study-finds/>)
    - Bristol value
Have I Fed My Cat Today will be an entirely separate app but with the exact same code :P
